UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304393297000056
KW  - Monetary policy
KW  - Inflation targeting
KW  - Rules and discretion
KW  - Central banking
AB  - The legislative framework under which the Reserve Bank of New Zealand operates was changed in 1989, to one providing for a tightly constructed target (rule), with discretion over instrument choice. The rationale for the change rests on the idea that damage to long-run growth would follow if monetary policy were to pay active attention to the short-run output and employment consequences of monetary policy actions. The rule now in place thus prohibits monetary policy from active consideration of output and employment as objectives in their own right. Initial results provide tentative evidence of the benefits of the approach.
ER  - 

